{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649116","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649116"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:01:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:01:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18349"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18349","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18349"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.68,0.18,0.05,0.05,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11067"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74331"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11067","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11067"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18349"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59822"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7472"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25671"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25674"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74331","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74331"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a dorsal muscle of the foot?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Extensor hallucis brevis","Flexor digitorum brevis","Abductor hallucis","Quadratus plantae","Flexor hallucis longus"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eextensor hallucis brevis\u003C/strong\u003E is a dorsal muscle of the foot, responsible for extending the big toe. It is located on the top of the foot and is part of the extensor group of muscles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eflexor digitorum brevis\u003C/strong\u003E is a plantar muscle, located on the sole of the foot, and is involved in flexing the toes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eabductor hallucis\u003C/strong\u003E is also a plantar muscle, located on the medial side of the foot, and is responsible for abducting the big toe.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Equadratus plantae\u003C/strong\u003E is a plantar muscle that assists in flexing the toes by modifying the pull of the flexor digitorum longus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eflexor hallucis longus\u003C/strong\u003E is a muscle located in the posterior compartment of the leg, and it flexes the big toe. It is not a dorsal muscle of the foot.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The extensor hallucis brevis is a dorsal muscle of the foot.","Dorsal muscles of the foot are involved in extending the toes."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of clinical and biochemical disorders of the skeleton. Oxford University Press","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59822"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18349"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanat